        <abstract> 
<p>Is slowly writing <hi rend="italic">Lythrum</hi> paper [<hi rend="italic">Collected papers</hi> 2: 106–31].</p> 
            <p>Thanks for [Charles?] Wright’s observations on orchids</p> 
<p>– could he note what attracts insects to <hi rend="italic">Begonia</hi> and <hi rend="italic">Melastoma</hi>? H. Crüger, who was going to observe Melastomataceae, has died.</p>  
<p>Describes the climbing habits of <hi rend="italic">Bignonia capreolata</hi> and <hi rend="italic">Eccremocarpus scaber</hi>.</p>  
<p>How does AG know the perfect flowers of <hi rend="italic">Voandzeia</hi> are quite sterile?</p> 
            <p>He has a case of dimorphism in holly; asks AG to report on American hollies.</p>
        </abstract>
